Chief justice David Maraga took office yesterday performing his first duty by swearing in members of panel tasked with selecting nominees to the electoral commission.The members of the selection panel are Evans Monari, Mary Kigen, justice (rtd) Tom Mbaluto, Bernadette Musundi, Rev Peter Karanja Mwangi, Prof Abdulghafur El-Busaidy, Bishop David Oginde and Rajesh Rawal.Earlier in the day, the CJ was received at the Supreme Court building by members of the Judicial Service Commission and judicial staff as he received the flag off the Supreme Court president.